<div id="review_2982123115" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2982123115" />
    <a title="Anne (On semi-hiatus)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2967061-anne-on-semi-hiatus"><img alt="Anne (On semi-hiatus)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1577653837p2/2967061.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2982123115?book_show_action=true">Apr 16, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anne (On semi-hiatus)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anne (On semi-hiatus)" href="/user/show/2967061-anne-on-semi-hiatus">Anne (On semi-hiatus)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2967061-anne-on-semi-hiatus?shelf=library">library</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2967061-anne-on-semi-hiatus?shelf=audio">audio</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2967061-anne-on-semi-hiatus?shelf=2020">2020</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2982123115" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17021681672858786344">There are so many reviews of this beloved book that all I will say is that I really enjoyed it. Those dear sweet elderly McPheron brothers with no experience with women or girls and birthing other than with their cows were the highlight of this book for me. Any time they were &quot;on stage&quot; I was smiling at their dear, sweet, sometimes bungling efforts to help and care for a young pregnant girl, Victoria. However, I cannot help but compare this book to a novella by the same author, <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/23602562.Our_Souls_at_Night' title='Our Souls at Night by Kent Haruf' rel='nofollow noopener'>Our Souls at Nigh</a></span>
  <span id="freeText17021681672858786344" style="display:none">There are so many reviews of this beloved book that all I will say is that I really enjoyed it. Those dear sweet elderly McPheron brothers with no experience with women or girls and birthing other than with their cows were the highlight of this book for me. Any time they were "on stage" I was smiling at their dear, sweet, sometimes bungling efforts to help and care for a young pregnant girl, Victoria. However, I cannot help but compare this book to a novella by the same author, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/23602562.Our_Souls_at_Night" title="Our Souls at Night by Kent Haruf" rel="nofollow noopener">Our Souls at Night</a> which I loved and was more deeply touched by and was a solid 5 star read for me. <br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="17021681672858786344" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
